home on  Portland Row in Dublin. The family celebrated her Tokyo win in the same way, surrounded by the overjoyed community. Photo: Mark Condren\n\nThere might be medals in Paris, but home is where the heart is, and that’s where boxer Kellie Harrington’s ­family will be supporting her from as she embarks on her second Olympic journey.\n\nThat home is on Portland Row in north inner-city Dublin, where the memories are still strong of everyone gathering at dawn in front of a big screen on August 8, 2021, to watch Harrington overcome the challenge of Beatriz Ferreira to win gold in Tokyo.", "title": "‘Home is where heart is’ for boxer Kellie Harrington’s family as Portland Row gears up for Olympics | Irish Independent", "top-image": "https://shared.mediahuis.be/logos/indo/v3/brand-main.svg", "domain": "www.independent.ie", "lang": "en", "author": "", "description": "There might be medals in Paris, but home is where the heart is, and that’s where boxer Kellie Harrington’s ­family will be supporting her from as she embarks on her second Olympic journey.", "keywords": "Kellie Harrington, Latest News Ticker, Paris 2024 Olympics"}